
  Name:  strlen
  
  #include <string.h>
  size_t strlen(const char *str);

  The strlen( ) function returns the length of the 
  null-terminated string pointed to by str. The nullterminator 
  is not counted.

  The following code fragment prints 5 on the screen:
   printf("%d", strlen("hello"));
      
  Related Functions:  memcpy,strchr,strcmp and strncmp.

